Description: How satisfied were you with the overall design process you experienced?
Value: The interface to select structural element is kind of tedious because there isn't any indications of element index. As the result, a user have to check each options to figure out which element is which.

Description: How easy was it to use the design tools provided?
Value: As stated in question 1, it isn't easy to use, nor to rotate

Description: How satisfied are you with the design decisions you made?
Value: I think it's logical to add bracings to the caltilevered structure, but some of the spaces don't necessarily have to be remove.

Description: How do you think having AI assistance would have changed your design process?
Value: I don't think AI in this case is better than a interactive and realtime structural analysis, at least the influence of AI is not that significant compared to facade design. I also don't think structural stability should be met by removing spaces.

Description: Would you choose to use this design process in future projects based on your current experience?
Value: Yes, I think the function of changing element in realtime is great, but I'll also use it with structural analysis.
